description:
Genuine Hickory Furniture 3 tier cabinet features beautiful bent wood curls, woven rattan inside and out, curved pencil reed base and unique inlaid wood handles. This is a high quality piece that has missing inlaid wood pieces, heavily scuffed surface on the base, areas with broken rattan, marks inside the cabinets and hole openings on the back panels. It is sturdy and all of the doors open and close well. It makes a great piece to restore, paint or lacquer.

*Shipping is not free. For long-distance shipping, please message me for a shipping quote. Local pickup or delivery is available in Fort Myers, FL.*

I have a second cabinet available that is in excellent condition: https://ellewoodworthy.etsy.com/listing/1568695886

I am Elle Woodworth and my husband and I are experts at rescuing vintage treasures. You may also call or text me at 239-560-2008 with any questions. 

SHIPPING:
Please message me for a shipping quote. We blanket wrap and carefully secure items for safe delivery to the 48 contiguous United States. We give you shipping updates as your item is being delivered.

LOCAL PICKUP:

RETURNS:
Cancellations are accepted within 24 hours of purchase. No returns or exchanges are accepted. Please contact me if you have any problems with your order. Upon receiving your item, it is your responsibility to fully inspect the piece of furniture before the shipper leaves and contact me immediately if there is an issue. 

We offer unique vintage items that may have imperfections. Please feel free to ask as many questions and request as many pictures as you'd like before ordering. I am happy to help. -Elle

title: 3 Yuji Hiratsuka 1993 Chine Collé Etchings Color intaglio WDI224-26
description:
Description: Yuji Hiratsuka was born in 1954 in Osaka, Japan. He has a B.S. in Art Education from Tokyo Gakugei University, and degrees in printmaking from New Mexico State University (MA) and Indiana University (MFA). He currently is a professor of printmaking at Oregon State University.  Hiratsuka has received numerous international awards. Since 2010 he has had 13 solo shows in the US, as well as in Korea, Canada and Northern Ireland. 
   
 Yuji Hiratsuka employs a distinctive printmaking technique, utilizing a mixed media approach that combines Chine Collé with etching. The artist himself provides a comprehensive description of this intricate and time-consuming printing process, showcasing his skill and experience.   
 
   "Suppose Pose"   
   "E Pose"   
   "Hi Pose"

title: Faux Bamboo Dresser by Henry Link Bali Hai 60" Long - 1970s Vintage Sage Green Hollywood Regency Coastal Chinoiserie Credenza with 9 Drawers
description:
Genuine Henry Link Bali Hai dresser features beautiful faux bamboo details, nine dovetailed drawers and its original brushed green finish. It is in very good vintage condition with some scuffs from normal wear and age and all of the drawers open and close well. Ready to be enjoyed in its original finish or it makes a great piece to paint or lacquer.

*Shipping is not free. For long-distance shipping, please message me your zip code for a shipping quote. Local pickup is available in Fort Myers, FL.*

•Measures 60" wide x 19.5" deep x 32.5" high.
•Drawer interior measurements: six outer drawers are 12" wide x 5" high x 14.5" deep and the three center drawers are 24.5" wide x 5" high x 14.5" deep. 
•Stamped "Henry Link" and "Bali Hai".
•All nine dovetailed drawers open and close smoothly.
•Includes its original hardware.
•Comes from a smoke free estate home.
•Great as a bedroom bureau, buffet cabinet, sideboard, credenza, media center or as a changing table for a nursery.

I am Elle Woodworth and my husband and I are experts at sourcing vintage treasures. Interested in seeing more? Meet us at our Fort Myers, FL warehouse to see all of our goodies! Call or text me at 239-560-2008 with any furniture questions or to schedule a time to meet.

SHIPPING:
Please message me for a shipping quote. We blanket wrap and carefully secure items for safe delivery to the 48 contiguous United States. We give you shipping updates as your item is being delivered.

LOCAL PICKUP 
We can meet in Fort Myers, FL.

RETURNS:
Cancellations are accepted within 24 hours of purchase. No returns or exchanges are accepted. Please contact me if you have any problems with your order. Upon receiving your item, it is your responsibility to fully inspect the piece before the furniture shipper leaves and contact me immediately if there is an issue. 

We offer unique vintage items that may have imperfections. Please feel free to ask as many questions and request as many pictures as you'd like before ordering. I am happy to help. -Elle

description:
The exquisite Hooker 'Bexar Leg Huntboard' Console Table, a true masterpiece for your home decor! This stunning piece features a rustic gambel oak finish with striking black highlights that add a touch of elegance to any space.    With its captivating design, this console table is sure to become the focal point of your living room, hallway, or entryway. The two drawers are adorned with beautifully carved floral designs, adding a hint of charm and     sophistication. They provide ample storage for your essentials, keeping your space organized and clutter-free.    Beneath the drawers, you'll find an open shelf, perfect for displaying your favorite books, decorative accents, or cherished photo frames. It's a versatile feature that allows you to showcase your personal style and add a personalized touch to your space.    One of the standout features of this console table is its six turned legs, which effortlessly blend traditional and contemporary styles. These sturdy legs not only provide exceptional stability but also add a touch of architectural beauty to the overall design.    Whether you're looking to enhance your farmhouse-inspired decor or add a touch of rustic charm to your modern space, the Hooker 'Bexar Leg Huntboard' Console Table is the perfect choice.

title: CHINESE COROMANDEL 4-PANEL SCREEN BY MAITLAND-SMITH, LTD. HK
description: Coromandel is named after the Coromandel Coast in South Eastern India from where the carved screens were originally dispatched to the West by European merchants. The art of making Coromandel requires a skilled hand, a trained eye and a great deal of patience. The frame of the screen is made from laminated wood, which is then sanded and sealed. A final coat is mixed with lime to solidify the sealer into a slate-hard finish.  This is followed by the application of 5 to 6 coats of fine Chinese clay, each layer troweled on smoothly and dried for a day before sanding. The entire preparation for each panel of the screen takes more than a week. Finally several layers of background color are applied and when dry, a rice paper drawing of the design to be incised is pasted onto the surface. The piece is now ready to be carved. Coromandel carvers are the most skilled of artists. They must carefully outline the faces and hands of sometimes minute figures, carving the smallest of details such as hair and foliage. They do this with the blade of a special knife which must not pierce the rice paper embedded under the thin layers of hardened lacquer and clay. When the carving is complete, bright colors are painted into the areas which have been carved out and gold leaf is skillfully applied to highlight the decoration. Finally, the piece is 'antiqued' to soften the colors and simulate the tone and finish of the ancient original coromandels.

title: Antique C. 1870s-1890s Tiger Oak Sideboard Cabinet Three Drawers Single Door Original Hardware Knapp Joinery True Craftsmanship
description:
Antique c. 1870s-1890s Tiger Oak Sideboard Cabinet Three Drawers Single Paneled Door Paneled Sides Original Hardware Knapp Joinery are a sign of a true quality craftsmanship

This is an antique piece of furniture that features drawers with a curious-looking half-circle joint, after some research we are certain that it was made in a North American factory between 1871 and 1900. The round pin hole came to be known as the Knapp Joint, the joint is also variously described by its appearance: the pin and cove, scallop and dowel, scallop and peg, pin and scallop, and half-moon.

However, this method of joinery was replaced by the mid 19th century, most furniture in America was made by machines in industrialized factories—with the exception of fine drawers. Machines that could produce dovetails were taking over and only high quality pieces were being made by hand. High-quality drawers were still being produced by hand, and while a skilled craftsman could turn out perhaps 20 drawers a day, that wasn’t nearly fast enough to keep pace with the production of furniture for which said drawers were intended. Handwork was holding up the factory output. That's pretty much the short history of Knapp joinery, you can be certain your pin and cove joinery is proof that you have an antique high quality piece of Americana.

title: French Bisque Porcelain Sculpture Moreau Woman w Basket JW169-10
description:
Early 20th century French biscuit porcelain sculpture Moreau depicting a woman with a basket of flowers. Rich, tactile detailing draws the eye of the viewer as only fine biscuit porcelain can. It was produced by the firm of Samson et Cie of Montreuil, France, probably between 1945 and 1969. Incised rear of plinth “Moreau”. Marked underside with “Genuine Biscuit Made in France” and a blue underglaze mark (crossed leafy branches over "S") of Samsom Cie, founded in Paris in the early 19th century. Measures 15in height x about 7in x 6in.   
 Dimensions: 6 x 6 x 15 
 Condition:  Repair at neck.  See photos 
 Local pick up Gaithersburg, MD.  Contact us for shipper suggestions.

title: AKG Harman K5500 MKIII Closed Back Reference Class Headphones LL127-46
description:
BRAND NEW.  Unopened.    
  With the K550MKIIIs, AKG® engineers have struck a masterful balance between the noise-isolating qualities of closed back headphones and the spacious, dimensional sound of an open-back design – creating reference-class headphones ideal for private listening both at home and on the go. 50mm drivers, the largest in our product line, deliver great AKG sound from your hi-fi system or virtually any portable device. The large ear cups and new headband design ensure an amazingly comfortable fit, and the 2D-Axis mechanism folds flat to stow or go.

title: Jolie-Varnish Topcoat-Low Luster-8oz
description:
Jolie-Varnish Topcoat-Low Luster-8oz    Jolie Varnish is a clear, water-based acrylic topcoat that creates a long-lasting finish on furniture and cabinetry. Available in two different sheen levels, it is perfect for projects that require a higher sheen.  Jolie Varnish is an easy to use alternative to a wax topcoat over Jolie Paint, stained, or raw wood.  For best results, apply 2-3 coats of Jolie Varnish with a synthetic bristle brush, such as a    Jolie Flat Brush , a sprayer, or a low nap roller.  Learn more:    How to Use Jolie Varnish   Please Note: Jolie Varnish may alter the hue of white paint colors, making them appear slightly warmer. If using Jolie Paint in any of our whites, we recommend sealing with    Jolie Finishing Wax    to avoid changes in color.   COVERAGE:    One 8oz (236.6ml) covers approximately 20-30 square feet (1.9-2.8 square meters).    One quart (946ml) covers approximately 100-125 square feet (9.3-11.6 square meters). One gallon (3.79 liters) covers approximately 450 square feet (41.8 square meters). Actual coverage may vary depending on surface and application.

title: Pair of Seguso Glass Column Lamps by Marbro
description:
Absolutely stunning pair of Marbro Seguso clear hand-blown art glass double socket table lamps with brass trim, circa 1960's!  These wonderful pieces of art come with large solid brass finials as well as hand-engraved detailed brass rings around each piece of hand blown glass, double pull chain sockets with on and off switches on the cords. Both lamps are stamped with the Marbro label in two separate areas.   Shades shown are included, but unknown if they are original or not. No price reduction if you don't want the shades.  Approximate dimensions: 37" high (top of finial) x 7" square base.  Condition: Overall very good condition with some minor age and use appropriate wear including patina in a few areas of the brass. Original wiring is in great working order.  One on/off cord switch has been replaced.  About Marbro Lamp Company:  The Marbro Lamp Company was one of the finest lamp producers during the mid-1900s. Its pieces were mainly sold in a handful of exclusive furniture shops. Marbro was the go-to supplier of Hollywood Regency and mid-century modern style lighting for interior designers. Its table lamps, chandeliers, floor lamps and wall sconces have graced the homes of many celebrities.

All four chairs fold for storage. Manufactured and hand built by Austin mfgr. of Mexico City. An intricate and flawless pattern of woven rush adorns this beautifully cherry finished palm wood. No cracks or breaks or splits. Solid cast brass fittings and hardware. A perfect accent to your Palm Springs patio, San Miguel Villa or Midwest Sun Room. Sturdy solid and beautifully finished. Although emulated in many iterations, this set looks to predate the Hans Wegner version. Made between 1940 - 1960 Includes 1 convertible table and 4 chairs.

Table measures 31.5 x 31.5 x 28.5 (game table)  31.5 x 31.5 x 18.5 (drinks table)

Price includes 4 chairs and 1 table

title: Late 19th Century Double Dragon Krater by Salviati
description: A spectacular 19th c. Murano krater from the venerable workrooms of Salviati.  Beautiful hues of cornflower blue and gold.   Mounted with gold flecked prunts and double dragons.  Intricately crafted wings and delicate red tongues.  A glorious centerpiece for a dining or entry table.   Part of a larger collection of dragon motif glass.

title: 1960s Pair of Tonala Cat Figurines
description: A beautiful pair of large Tonala cats with striking fantasia style painting.  Inquisitive eyes and sweet smiles are the hallmarks of these classic figures.  Made in Jalsisco and hand painted.  One is signed Solis the other is by Ken Edwards.  Both made in the 1960s.  The larger cat has some hairline cracks but is extremely stable.  The smaller cat is perfect.

title: Chrome Pedestals Milo Baughman - A Pair

title: Late 19th Century Venetian Dragon Bowls - Set of 4

These delicate creatures have survived the past century with wings and tongues intact.  A stunning group that can be used as decorative objects or added to your dining table for extra ooomph.  Frilled rims mounted with a unique dragon.

title: Mid 20th Century Robsjohn-Gibbings Geometric Side Table

title: 1980s Dan Abramson Postmodernist Bar Cabinet
description: California Design meets Post Modernism in this beautiful two piece cabinet / altar, handcrafted  from recycled wood in the 1980s with polychromed finish by Artist Dan Abramson. title: 1950s Italian Side Chairs- a Pair

title: 1930s Malian Chi-Wara Head Crests- a Pair
description:
Ethnographic work of art by Bambara people;  The Ch-wara headcrest is a symbol spring, rebirth and an excellent harvest.  A chimera representing a combination of Antelope, Aardvark and Pangolin, the Chi-Wara headcrest is a beautifully sculptural object.  From the 1920's 30s, this pairs geometric rhythm suggest the art deco influence of early modernity.  Both headcrests are stably set into metal pedestals, one in steel and the other in solid bronze.

Steel Base: 39" x 12" x 4"

title: PETER DUNHAM HOLLYWOOD HOME PAPER RUSH BLK SIDE CHAIR set 8
description:
The set is from his "Hollywood at Home" collection & one his best known designs. They are the his How to Marry a Millionaire Paper Rush side Chair in the ebonized charcoal colorway. The current listing price retail is $2700 a chair plus $300 per custom cushion (featuring a down fill with a blue and white aztec print).

Details:Paper Rush Woven Side Chair Black & Beige Dining Chairs - Set of 8

Pick up in Santa Monica can also coordinate delivery within 5 mile radius

*also comes with custom cushions as well that are peter dunham fabric blue and white aztec print see photos

Details: A re-edition of a chair bought at a Hollywood memorabilia auction and attributed to legendary designer, T. H. Robsjohn-Gibbings. The original was made famous in a scene of the 1953 hit movie How to Marry a Millionaire featuring Lauren Bacall and Marilyn Monroe. The deceptively comfortable chair is made by hand in Los Angeles with oak and paper rush.

Note: Custom cushions are available as well.

Whats in the set: Set of 8, which includes two end chairs with arm rests, & 6 side chairs.

Each: $2700 retail

title: Accent Table (Dark Taupe Finish)
description:
Elevate Your Home Decor with Accent Furniture 
 From your bedroom to your living room, we all know that—when it comes to design—small details matter the most. While a bedframe draws attention and a couch catches the eye, accent furniture is the cinch that pulls a room together. To elevate your home décor with accent furniture, choose a side table or nightstand to place alongside bigger furniture. For a dynamic design, choose furniture in wood stains and colors that complement, but don’t precisely match, the other pieces in the room. Then, arrange smaller pieces, like lamps, books, pottery, or florals, on top for that seamlessly luxurious look. Beautiful, long-lasting tables that fit into any room.

title: Signed Armando Pena Mixed Media Embossed Monotype Print on Handmade Paper VR49-10884
description:
Description  : Amado Pena Jr. American Artist: B. 1943. Amado Pena Jr.'s art focuses on Hispanic and Native American figures and has been described as capturing the essence of the Southwest. Pena, a mestizo of Mexican and Yaqui Indian descent, was born in 1943 and raised in Laredo, Texas. He earned B.A. and M.A. degrees at Texas A & I University in Kingsville, Texas and was an art teacher in Texas public schools for sixteen years. Pena is known for his humanitarian efforts, and his fund-raising activities have benefited charities such as the March of Dimes, Juvenile Diabetes Foundation, Native American Rights Fund and the Mexican American Legal and Educational Fund. The Amado and JB Pena "Art Has Heart" Foundation, established in 1994, provides opportunities for low and modest income students in Texas, New Mexico, Colorado and Arizona to further their education in the arts. Listings wanted.

title: Omega Seamaster Automatic Stainless Watch 14770-2SC cal.562 1961 HH191-1
description:
This Omega was made in 1962. This particular case model, the 14770, is known as a transition model from a “pre-de Ville” Seamaster to the Seamaster De Ville, meaning some dials would have or not have a “de Ville” under the Seamaster text. Only produced between 1960-1962. This watch is a masterful combination of strength and elegance, says Omega’s 1960’s marketing team. 
 
 
 
  
 
 
 
  There are printed minute marks around the dial and beautifully applied hour baton indices, with obelisk shaped indices for the 12, 6, and 9. Below the 12, the applied Omega logo is in gold, matching the champagne dial. Above the 6, you have the word “Seamaster” which in this model, collectors describe as the “coat hanger S” and “swiss made” is proudly found below the 6 o’clock.   
  Condition:  Very good.  
  Local pick up Bethesda, MD.  We will ship at buyer's expense.

title: Lithograph Print Picasso Woman Portrait de Mille D.M Dora Maar GH113-4
description:
When Dora Maar met Pablo Picasso she was 28 years old, younger than the established painter by over two decades. They met through a shared interest in the surrealist movement; the stunning muse was a painter and photographer, herself. Having been introduced for the first time in 1936, this would be one of his earliest portraits of Dora, before the infamous and more extreme representations of her seen in his later work. Despite the gap in age, this stunning work captures the profound connection between Picasso and Dora. In stylistic terms this piece is referential the Blue Period, but through a cubist gaze. Almost monochromatic, the cool and austere coloration evokes a solemn and introspective tone. Through truncation and exaggeration, Dora’s piercing eyes are emphasized, expressing this somber portrait’s depth of character and inner beauty. 
 PABLO PICASSO - PORTRAIT DE DORA MAAR 1936 PRINT #2091, COLLECTIBLE ART 
 COLOUR IMAGE ON PAPER, FINE ART GRAPHIC REPRODUCTION, FRAMED WITH GLASS, OFFSET LITHOGRAPH
   
 
 Dimensions: FRAME - 18" X 16"/ PRINT - 8" X 10" (HEAVY)

title: Leroy Neiman Caspian Tiger Pencil Signed Framed & Numbered KS83-2
description:
Extremely Rare and Original Serigraph in colors by LeRoy Neiman titled, "Caspian Tiger" from his tribute to the jungle, and its most majestic animals. Numbered 141 / 375. Published in 1986, it is now nearly impossible to find. Thus, it might be your last opportunity to purchase this serigraph, especially for significantly less than the current retail of $11,000.00.   
  LEROY NEIMAN (1926 - 2012): Leroy Neiman is best known for his brilliantly colored, stunningly energetic images of sporting events, social and leisure activities. During his lifetime, he was the most popular and successful living artist in the United States. Neiman's artistic style and genius is familiar to a remarkably broad spectrum of people around the world. His artworks are found in monthly issues of playboy magazine, has been used in promotion for the Olympics and Super Bowl and completed along the sidelines of many other sporting events. Neiman was widely regarded as the greatest living artist at the time of his death in 2012. The Prestigious Heritage Auction House has recently stated, "Though Neiman has long served as the most recognizable American artist of the post-war era, his recent passing has added rocket fuel to the fire of his market, with four of his works soaring into six-figure territory in recent Heritage auctions. We expect the climb in pricing to continue, and for smart investors to be paying close attention when this classic work hits the block."   
  DIMENSIONS: 43" x 36"H   
  CONDITION: Please refer to photos for a more detailed look at condition. We make every attempt to list and photograph any defects or signs of wear that are significant to this sale.  
  LOCAL PICKUP BETHESDA, MD.  Contact us for shipper suggestions.

title: Jiang "Speed" Color Serigraph on Art Paper Hand Signed KS83-15
description:
Color Serigraph on Art Paper titled "Speed" from his paying homage to mother nature and her most majestic animals. Worth mentioning again is the fact that Jiang is widely regarded as one of the greatest Chinese artists ever and the father of their Pop Art movement. And, therefore, his artworks have sold into the 100,000s of dollars.   
  This piece is an ORIGINAL, HAND SIGNED and NUMBERED Serigraph that is representative of Jiang's full realm of genius, including technique and detail. The incredible work of art, from the rare edition of 260 (#11), is guaranteed authentic, and accompanying the purchase, the buyer shall receive a Gallery letter of authenticity. Also, it is of impressive size measuring 20" x 40" and is complimented by a custom frame with approximate dimensions of 30" x 50". Jiang, Tie Feng Jiang Tie Feng was an elder statesman of the now famous Yunnan School and Heavy Color Movement, which revolutionized Chinese painting in the 1980 s. A professor at the Academy of Fine Arts, Beijing, and the creator of the national monument Stone Forest in the Great Hall of the People, Tian-an-men Square. Jiang Tie Feng is also the leading subject of scholarly surveys of the contemporary revolution in Chinese painting.  
   Both art and frame are in very good condition. Please look closely at the images for a more detailed look.

title: Baltic Amber Multi-Strand Necklace Reverse Intaglio Portrait Carving
description:
This vintage heirloom-quality necklace is both refined and eye-catching, an elegant keepsake piece. It was handcrafted with eight strands of Baltic amber beads in graduated tones of red and orange. The strands are held in place by four amber bars across the front that create a beautiful draped effect. The necklace is doubly secured with a long sterling silver clasp as well as a safety chain.  Set at the bottom is a large 2.25" x 1.875" x .75"(d) oval reverse intaglio portrait carving of a female bust. Because the carving is done in reverse Intaglio style on the back of the amber, the surface of the amber will feel smooth to the touch and the cameo carving is protected from wear. The carving was skillfully done the old fashioned way, not laser etched.  If you look through the back of the pendant, inclusions that are typical in natural amber can be enjoyed, such as a few gorgeous sun-spangles.   The necklace was purchased 16 - 20 years ago at Uncommon Treasures in Portland and is still in excellent condition, with the natural warm patina of vintage sterling silver.   An interesting fact about amber is that most of the world's amber is in the range of 30-90 million years old.#A. title: Art Nouveau Amethyst & Garnet Handcast Pendant & Chain by Bob Stringer
description:
This vintage, custom-made one-of-a-kind sterling silver double-sided pendant by Bob Stringer is an amazing piece of craftsmanship showcasing an Art Nouveau motif on one side using leaves, floral, cherub & fairy characters. The other side features an elaborate fish design using filigree accents and details. Each piece is hand cast and applied individually.  The pendant is set with two natural amethyst cabochons, one 9mm round and one 12x14mm oval shape; and a  large terminated amethyst crystal that measures ~20mm x 11mm x 11mm; all of which are natural in origin and have a strong purple color. The amethyst gemstones weigh roughly 33.50 carats in all.   Also set in the pendant are eight round 2.8mm natural spessartite garnet gemstones with a reddish-orange color and a combined weight of .96 carats.  The pendant is in excellent condition, measures 2.75"(l) x 1.375"(w), and is suspended on a 20" box style chain. Both the pendant and the chain exhibit the natural warm patina of vintage sterling silver. #A.

title: 3.36ctw Emerald .36ctwDiamond 14K Yellow Gold Slide Pendant
description:
This three-dimensional 14 karat yellow gold heart-shaped slide pendant is set with ninety-four natural emerald gemstones and twenty-nine natural diamonds. The diamonds are set in 14 karat white gold heart settings on the yellow gold heart shape. Overall the pendant measures 1.25" x 1.25". (Chain not included). title: 2.29ct Citrine .34ct Ant Hill Garnet 14K Yellow Gold Articulated Pendant
description:
This skillfully crafted two-piece, articulated, 14 karat yellow gold pendant is set with one 13.5mm x 7mm, 2.29ct., pear-shaped yellowish-orange natural citrine gemstone and one 4mm, .34ct., round brilliant natural ant hill red garnet gemstone. Pendant measures 1.75"(l) x .625"(w). #90, #A.  The artisan for this piece shared with me the origin of the name "ant hill garnet", such as the one used in this piece. I found it quite fascinating, and perhaps you will, too.   Some gems derive a large portion of their appeal because they are found in an unexpected locality or have an unusual origin. This particular red garnet derives its name because they are found on and around the margins of ant hills. The ants encounter them while excavating their underground passages, and in order to rid their passages of these inconvenient obstacles, the ants haul the stones to the surface and discard them. The rain washes the garnets clean and moves them down the flank of the ant hill, where they can accumulate in large numbers. This concentrates the little gems and makes them easy for people to collect. Their brilliant luster and red color contrasts strongly with the surrounding soil. Source: Geology.com

title: "Goddess of Compassion" Guan Yin Buddha Jadeite .85ctw Diamond 18K Gold Pendant
description:
This high-end 18 karat yellow gold pendant depicts a timeless symbol seen in jade, the Guan Yin. The goddess represents compassion, kindness and mercy. It is believed that the goddess has vowed to save and protect  the wearer, and in addition, the Guan Yin pendant encourages the wearer to practice patience and kindness on a daily basis. The jadeite jade carving measures ~ 2.0"(l) x 1.125" - .25"(w) and weighs approximately 78-80 carats.  The 18 karat yellow gold setting has been beautifully crafted with ornate details. Along the top and bottom of the pendant are set thirty-seven round brilliant cut diamonds that adorn the goddess' headdress and the lotus upon which she sits. The diamonds weigh .85 carats are of a bright white G-H color and SI clarity. The back of the pendant features an elaborate and substantial 18 karat yellow gold open back design that protects the breadth of the carving.   The carving is exceptional and the pendant is in excellent condition. The overall dimensions of the pendant are 2.875" x 1.125".#A.  The consignor has advised that the jade was graded as Type B jade by Bonhams, meaning that the original color of the jade has not been altered.

title: Wrought Iron Console/Entry Table Dark Pewter Gold Finish Stone Veneer Top
description: This wrought iron console/entry table is a testament to timeless elegance and meticulous craftsmanship. The sturdy wrought iron frame, meticulously forged with intricate scrolls and curves, exudes a sense of enduring strength and grace. Its dark pewter gold finish adds a touch of opulence, casting a subtle sheen that enhances the table's sophisticated presence. The crowning glory is the stone veneer top, seamlessly integrated to provide a luxurious surface. The natural beauty of the stone veneer, with its rich textures and earthy tones, adds depth and character to the table, making it a striking focal point in any space. This console table effortlessly blends classic design with contemporary allure, making it a statement piece that transcends trends and stands as a testament to refined taste.

title: Modern Demilune Sideboard/Buffet Empire Style with 2 Drawers Side Cabinets and Original Hardware
description:
This exquisite Demilune sideboard/buffet seamlessly blends classical elegance with a touch of Empire sophistication. The Demilune sideboard/buffet silhouette creates a harmonious balance between the curved front and flat back, making it an ideal choice for placement against a wall or in a corner. Crafted from rich hardwood the sideboard/buffet exhibits a lustrous finish that radiates a warm and inviting glow. The meticulous craftsmanship is evident in every inch, showcasing the artisan's dedication to both form and function.
Adding a regal touch, the Empire handles draw inspiration from the neoclassical Empire style. These handles are characterized by their bold, geometric shapes and intricate detailing. Crafted with precision, they serve as both functional elements and ornate embellishments, enhancing the overall grandeur of the sideboard/buffet.
Opening the sideboard/buffet reveals a well-thought-out interior designed for practicality.  Two drawers and adjustable shelves provide customizable storage space, accommodating a variety of items with ease. Whether used to showcase cherished collectibles or to stow away essentials, the Demilune sideboard/buffet seamlessly merges form and function.

description:
Description:  NEW IN BOX.  Chic while balancing the concepts of geometrics and eclecticism, the Zanadoo Outdoor Pendant by Arteriors delivers full-fledged visual appeal to contemporary outdoor settings. The piece resembles a star encased in a glass box, with the framework of the box comprised of a steel frame and clear glass panels. Within the box is a starburst design with multiple spindles and rods protruding outwards. Fixture utilizes a total of 12 incandescent bulbs (not included) to supply the immediate area with warm, ambient type of light. 
 
 
  Features  
 
 Constructed from steel 
 Includes a glass shade 
 (12) 40 watt maximum candelabra (E12) bulbs required 
 Includes (1) 4", (1) 6", and (2) 12" downrods

 Covered under a 1 year limited manufacturer warranty

title: 1970s Phyllis Morris San Simoen Griffin Gold Leaf Console/Sofa Table
description: The designer of this unique piece is none other than, Phyllis Morris (born October 19, 1925 in Chicago, Illinois; died September 5, 1988 in Los Angeles California).  She was an American furniture designer known for her colorful persona, her outspokenness on decorating and her distinctive furniture and interior designs.  She was often referred to by the media as the "designer to the stars." By the time of her death, Morris had left a mark in the world of interior design in each of the four decades since the founding of her company Phyllis Morris Originals in 1953.  As anyone can see, she had a designer persona all her own, which embody the spirit of Hollywood Regency and California eclectic styles combined with her interpretation of Baroque-meets-Fantasy style.  Personally, I want it, yet, that would be considered, "high treason!".

title: 1950s A. Brandt Ranch "Cowboy Classics" Oak Arm Chair
description:
The light oak color, referred to as Natural Oak, finished with white wax detailing, was believed to be produced, circa 1950's. It's natural oak finish and white wax is still visible, a handsome example of an "A. Brandt" arm chair. These chairs were built to be indestructible, and still are desirable. This chair shows minor wear and would be a handsome addition to any home. 
 A little about the A. Brandt Company, Inc.’s. The Ranch Oak line debuted in Fort Worth, TX in 1938 and continued being manufactured into the early 1980’s. In 1986 the company was sold. From Wolf Ranch Oak, "Many of the earliest furniture designs depicted icons of ranch life carved into oak. Pictorial carvings included horses, horse heads and horseshoes, longhorns, campfires, saguaro and prickly pear cactus, and even a western scene of a cowboy riding a bucking bronco. By 1970, it seems likely from looking through factory catalogs that very few if any western motif-carved pieces were still being produced."

title: 1980s Vintage Custom Square Metal Bronze Coffee Table With Geometric Copper and Silver Square and Rectangular Patterns
description:
Found this unique vintage gem at an auction in Southern California, was visiting beaches and photographing coastal views. During viewing the session I found this coffee table and was struck by the geometric patterns and searched for examples of this on my phone, what I found surprised me - it can be found in various cultures and time periods, including ancient civilizations like the Egyptians and Greeks, as well as modern and contemporary art movements. Wow. I read on,Geometric art often emphasizes symmetry, order, and precision. It explores the relationships between shapes, lines, colors, and proportions. Artists working in this style may use basic geometric shapes such as squares, circles, triangles, or more complex forms like polygons, spirals, or fractals. Wow.
That sold me,  not only is the piece striking, optically pleasant but structurally sound. All metal, including the legs. I lifted one side, it was heavy then I looked at the underside and discovered that the legs can be taken apart held together by hex nuts and bolts. Very sturdy. I decided I had to have that piece and my wife agreed. Wow. We waited for a while before the lot came up and the bidding began. The bidding war began slowly and build into a frenzy (don't they always) in the end I took it apart and loaded it onto my pickup truck. Came home a winner.

title: Vintage Safari Style Wine Cabinet Faux Leather Crocodile Imprint Elephant Head Pedestal – 2 Pieces
description:
The word, unique, is a starting point, for this ruggedly handsome piece.  African inspired wine cabinet with a stylistic faux crocodile leather imprint covering with faux tusks handles on the doors of the cabinet sitting atop a pedestal of great elephant heads in patina style as legs.  Wow, what else can you say. Yet, when you open the doors, you are struck with the form and function - glasses above and a wine rack below with enough elbow room for your favorite liqueurs. All this coming from this burly, brawny, and commanding cabinet - placed in just the right room in your house. What a statement you will make…
It conjures images of Hemingway, struggling to write the best passage from his home in Key West, for his next new book.  Visualizing scenes of snow-covered summits, hyenas, lions and elephants… He pauses, reaches for a drink and discovers it empty gets up and strolls to his safari style wine cabinet and pours himself a glass of Cinzano on the rocks.

title: Vintage 1991 Bauer Hollywood Regency Styled Stacked Lucite and Brass Table Lamp With Brass Base and Cover
description:
This distinctive item is made of lucite (liquid plastic) and are designed with extraordinary care. In the Bauer  Lamp Company lighting catalog, there are many options to choose from, but this one is stunning and in beautiful condition surviving three decades of human care, which at times an be lethal for vintage pieces. The original brass base and cover are in wonderful condition.  The lucite pieces are still very clear and make for a striking design.
What is Lucite?  I thought it was plastic, but now I know, Lucite is the tradename of polymethyl methacrylate. Other well-known trade names are Crylux, Plexiglass, Acrylite, and Perspex. It is a transparent thermoplastic polymer. It is important as an alternative to glass in its sheet form.  There you go - now you know what Lucite is.

title: 1970s Hollywood Regency Chrome Base and Beveled Glass Coffee Table
description:
This vintage piece is a great example of Hollywood Regency and is in excellent condition. Yet, shopping for a coffee table requires some thought. How big is your living room, rule of thumb 16-18" from sofa and 30" from fireplace or flat screen. Sectionals look great with round tables. If you have kiddos in the house a round table is better than rectangular - no sharp edges. Consider the height of the coffee table (CT), if you bend down to get your glass and fall over - then it probably to low. Our CT is a nice height of 24" certainly not too low.
The glass is a hefty 3/4" thick and is very stable on it's beautifully sculptured chrome base. Don't pretend it won't look good in your living room.

description: Our antique drum table belongs in the same category as the circular multi sided library tables with several drawers actually two drawers in alternating fashion. Between each drawer is dummy drawers, as was typical in those designs. You can have only so many working drawers before running out of room. These antique tables were first introduced in the late 18th century and have a rotating leather or inlay top, standing on a central turned pedestal. The main timber used in construction was Mahogany, usually with veneered drawer fronts and edges. The best quality antique drum tables have oak drawer linings and quality brass handles, I happy to inform you that this item has both.  However, the storage space of the drawers is small for writing pads and pens or a good place to store playing cards. These antique tables were first introduced in the late 18th century and have a rotating top, standing on a central turned pedestal. They are referred to as ‘rent tables’, as traditionally they were used by landlords to keep the accounts of rent money due and paid.  A handsome piece ready to adorn any space in your home.

title: Tall Neoclassic Style Heavy Ceramic Black Colored Vases/Urns Mounted to Round Brass Bottoms Accented by Extended Brass Handles - A Pair
description:
As the Rococo style was in decline, archaeological discoveries, particularly uncovered sites at Pompeii and Herculaneum, stimulated the minds of craftsmen and designers across Europe. Also, widespread travel occurred with Westerners visiting Italy, Greece, and the Middle East. At the same time, a veritable slew of publications in Europe covering these archaeological digs and publishing about these finds. Overall, there was a massively increased interest in the Classical Era at this time. 
 The “Grand Tour” of Europe, which intellectuals and aristocrats saw as part of the education of the modern European gentleman, comprised an extended visit to Rome, among other places, and many went on to Greece. This led them through a haven of Classical design styles and motifs. Everyone wanted to experience the beauty of the Hellenic Period back at home.
 The neoclassic style developed in France then quickly spread throughout Europe and to the United States. Enjoy our vases for they are a beautiful way to celebrate an important period in humankind.

title: Anatoly Metlan "Restaurant Row" Framed  Serigraph on Paper VR49-10881
description:
Description  : Anatoly Metlan was born in Yalta in 1964. From a young age he showed artistic abilities therefore he went to art school, and later on studied at the Krivoi Rog University in the Ukraine. During his schooling he began to show his art in exhibitions, and in 1989 he was accepted into the National Artists Guild in the Ukraine. Furthermore, after the collapse of the USSR, Metlan and his family moved to Israel in 1991 where he still lives today. Metlan’s art is inspired by traveling and the cultural experiences he gains through these trips. His most famous works include landscape paintings of the Mediterranean and paintings of dancers from Spanish-speaking cultures all done in vivid rich colors.
